<figureCitation id="A3922A050D12B610FDB3F80CFD42FB44" box="[624,708,1130,1157]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1994,2016]" captionTargetBox="[170,1416,203,1951]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[151,1436,190,1970]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Geographic distribution in the Mexican territory of: A. H. micranthum, L. aristatum, L. berlandieri var. filifolium, L. longipes, and L. rupestre; B. L. australe, L. australe var. glandulosum, L. flagellare, L. nelsonii, and L. usitatissimum. Maps by Ma. Isabel Olivares." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6622759" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6622759/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="149">Fig. 2b</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B1636800D12B610FF7EF8EBFC36FB31" blockId="8.[136,1452,1057,1912]" pageId="8" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis id="09DDEA920D12B610FF7EF8EBFE38FB69" bold="true" box="[189,446,1165,1192]" pageId="8" pageNumber="149">Habitat and ecology:</emphasis>
—Cypress-juniper forest, oak-pine forests, prickly-pear cactus patches, grasslands, oak forests, thornless small-leaved shrubland, and pine forests. Elevation 
<quantity id="FC519B650D12B610FC67F8D4FBC2FB0D" box="[932,1092,1202,1229]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.075" metricValueMax="2.65" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="149" unit="m" value="2075.0" valueMax="2650.0" valueMin="1500.0">1500–2650 m</quantity>
. Montane soils, mainly red-ash Acrisol, Andosol, Cambisol, Phaeozem, Lithosol, Luvisol, and Regosol.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B1636800D12B610FF7EF89CFCC6FAD5" blockId="8.[136,1452,1057,1912]" box="[189,832,1274,1300]" pageId="8" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis id="09DDEA920D12B610FF7EF89CFEC5FAD5" bold="true" box="[189,323,1274,1300]" pageId="8" pageNumber="149">Phenology:</emphasis>
—Flowering and fruiting in May–September.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B1636800D12B610FF7EF97BFBB2FA9D" blockId="8.[136,1452,1057,1912]" pageId="8" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis id="09DDEA920D12B610FF7EF97BFE05FAF9" bold="true" box="[189,387,1309,1336]" pageId="8" pageNumber="149">Taxonomic note:</emphasis>
—The black and prominent stipular glands of 
<taxonomicName id="FCA94D030D12B610FC42F979FB46FAF9" box="[897,1216,1310,1336]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Linaceae" genus="Mesynium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="149" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="australe" variety="glandulosum">
<emphasis id="09DDEA920D12B610FC42F979FC7CFAF9" box="[897,1018,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="149">L. australe</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="09DDEA920D12B610FBECF978FB46FAF9" box="[1071,1216,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="149">glandulosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the nodes, leaves, bracts, and sepals make it possible to clearly differentiate this variety of the species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B1636800D12B610FF7EF903FB05F9D1" blockId="8.[136,1452,1057,1912]" pageId="8" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis id="09DDEA920D12B610FF7EF903FE34FA41" bold="true" box="[189,434,1381,1408]" pageId="8" pageNumber="149">Conservation status:</emphasis>
— 
<bibRefCitation id="5F384B710D12B610FE0CF900FC44FA41" author="Rzedowski, J. &amp; Calderon de Rzedowski, G." box="[463,962,1382,1408]" pageId="8" pageNumber="149" pagination="1 - 22" refId="ref43536" refString="Rzedowski, J. &amp; Calderon de Rzedowski, G. (1992) Linaceae. In: Rzedowki, J. &amp; Calderon de Rzedowski, G. (Eds.) Flora del Bajio y de Regiones Adyacentes. Fasciculo 6: 1 - 22. [ISBN: 0188 - 5170]" type="journal article" year="1992">Rzedowski &amp; Calderón de Rzedowski (1992)</bibRefCitation>
mention that 
<taxonomicName id="FCA94D030D12B610FB9BF901FA12FA41" box="[1112,1428,1382,1408]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Linaceae" genus="Mesynium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="8" pageNumber="149" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="australe" variety="glandulosum">
<emphasis id="09DDEA920D12B610FB9BF901FB49FA41" box="[1112,1231,1382,1408]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="149">L. australe</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="09DDEA920D12B610FAC0F900FA12FA41" box="[1283,1428,1382,1408]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="149">glandulosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is at risk of extinction. However, according to the criteria established by the 
<bibRefCitation id="5F384B710D12B610FC79F9ECFBC9FA65" author="IUCN" box="[954,1103,1418,1444]" pageId="8" pageNumber="149" refId="ref41972" refString="IUCN (2019) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee. Downloadable from: https: // www. iucnredlist. org / resources / redlistguidelines (accessed 22 April 2022)" type="url" year="2019">IUCN (2019)</bibRefCitation>
this variety is Vulnerable (VU) (B2abc(iii)), with an EOO of 
<quantity id="FC519B650D12B610FE14F9C8FD09FA09" box="[471,655,1454,1481]" metricMagnitude="8" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.64257374" pageId="8" pageNumber="149" unit="km" value="164257.374">164,257.374 km</quantity>
<superScript id="CCDC9BC80D12B610FD4CF9C8FD11FA7D" attach="left" box="[655,663,1454,1468]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="149">2</superScript>
and AOO of 
<quantity id="FC519B650D12B610FCF3F9C8FCFEFA09" box="[816,888,1454,1480]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="8" pageNumber="149" unit="km" value="28.0">28 km</quantity>
<superScript id="CCDC9BC80D12B610FCBBF9C8FC06FA7D" attach="left" box="[888,896,1454,1468]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="149">2</superScript>
, known to &lt;10 localities. It is worth mentioning that its distribution in areas that harbor large human population nuclei of the country and the constant loss of habitat (
<bibRefCitation id="5F384B710D12B610FF53F990FED5F9D1" author="CONABIO" box="[144,339,1526,1552]" pageId="8" pageNumber="149" refId="ref41122" refString="CONABIO (2021) Indice de Impacto Humano en la Biodiversidad Terrestre. Comision Nacional para uso y conocimiento de la Biodiversidad. Available from: http: // geoportal. conabio. gob. mx / metadatos / doc / html / indihum 14 gw. html (accessed 1 December 2021)" type="url" year="2021">CONABIO 2021</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="5F384B710D12B610FE9DF990FD7AF9D1" author="Rodriguez-Echeverry, J. &amp; Leiton, M." box="[350,764,1526,1552]" pageId="8" pageNumber="149" pagination="923449" refId="ref42991" refString="Rodriguez-Echeverry, J. &amp; Leiton, M. (2021) Perdida y fragmentacion de ecosistemas boscosos nativos y su influencia en la diversidad de habitats en el hotspot Andes tropicales. Revista Mexicana de Biodiversidad 92: e 923449. https: // doi. org / 10.22201 / ib. 20078706 e. 2021.92.3449" type="journal article" year="2021">Rodríguez-Echeverry &amp; Leiton 2021</bibRefCitation>
) could be a cause of threat shortly.
</paragraph>
